			</div><div id="location" class="et_pb_section et_pb_section_1 et_pb_with_background et_section_regular">
				
				
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_row et_pb_row_4">

				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_3  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_light">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner"><h2><span data-metadata="<!--(figmeta)eyJmaWxlS2V5Ijoid24zaGh5czM3NzVHdXp6RHh5dm0zTiIsInBhc3RlSUQiOjczNTA1MzM3OCwiZGF0YVR5cGUiOiJzY2VuZSJ9Cg==(/figmeta)-->"></span><span data-buffer="<!--(figma)(/figma)-->"></span>Where is Shaws Braddell Heights Located?</h2></div>
			</div>
			</div>
				
				
				
				
			</div><div class="et_pb_row et_pb_row_5">
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_3_5 et_pb_column_6  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_4  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_light">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner"><p>Picture a quiet pristine neighbourhood, framed by lush tropical trees, away from the noise and heavy traffic. That is where Shaws Braddell Heights is located at: 24 Lynwood Grove, in a cosy little cottage within the idyllic Braddell Heights residential estate in Serangoon.</p>
<p>Established in 1990, Shaws Preschool at Braddell was one of the first play-based schools in Singapore. Every aspect of our preschool is designed for our children to discover experiential learning through play and adventure.</p>
<p>Located away from the bustling city, the children get to be among nature in the serene surrounding environment. The morning walk to our school is always a calming one, soothed by the sounds of birds chirping and leaves rustling. Often, our children are greeted by our friendly neighbours while they do their morning runs or a spot of gardening.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The school itself has a big field for our children to expend their energy in. Some of the activities the little ones do here include all manner of sports, sandplay, waterplay and outdoor play. On some days, if you are lucky, you can spot hornbills on the tree, squirrels scurrying on the fence, and even inquisitive parakeets chirping!</p></div>
			</div>
			</div><div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_2_5 et_pb_column_7  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough et-last-child">

				<div class="et_pb_text_inner"><h2>What Are the Unique Features of Shaws Braddell Heights?</h2></div>
			</div>
			</div>
				
				
				
				
			</div><div class="et_pb_row et_pb_row_7">
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_2 et_pb_column_9  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_image et_pb_image_0 box-blue">
				
				
				
				
				<span class="et_pb_image_wrap "><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="510" height="492" src="https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/children-exercising-1024x987-1-12-2-min.jpg" data-src="https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/children-exercising-1024x987-1-12-2-min.jpg" alt="Children exercising in the field" title="children-exercising-1024x987-1-(12) (2)-min" data-srcset="https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/children-exercising-1024x987-1-12-2-min.jpg 510w, https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/children-exercising-1024x987-1-12-2-min-480x463.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 510px, 100vw" class="wp-image-11485 lazyloaded" srcset="https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/children-exercising-1024x987-1-12-2-min.jpg 510w, https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/children-exercising-1024x987-1-12-2-min-480x463.jpg 480w"><noscript><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="510" height="492" src="https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/children-exercising-1024x987-1-12-2-min.jpg" alt="Children exercising in the field" title="children-exercising-1024x987-1-(12) (2)-min" srcset="https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/children-exercising-1024x987-1-12-2-min.jpg 510w, https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/children-exercising-1024x987-1-12-2-min-480x463.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 510px, 100vw" class="wp-image-11485 lazyload" /></noscript></span>
			</div>
			</div><div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_2 et_pb_column_10  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough et-last-child">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_6  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_light">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner"><p>Shaws Braddell Heights stands out with our expansive field that allows for numerous outdoor activities for our children, such as sports, gardening, mud play and waterplay. Even under the strict COVID-19 guidelines, our children could still spend quality time in the open spaces daily for outdoor play. Now that restrictions are slightly eased, we have resumed most activities while taking the right precautions and safety measures.</p>
<p>Our sandpit and mud kitchen offer the little ones outlets to get their creative juices flowing, while our long and wide driveway is great for tricycle play and messy play activities. We also hold Messy Play and Little League (Sports) activities every week on Thursdays and Fridays. Our kids are always looking forward to that!</p></div>

			</div><div id="typical-program" class="et_pb_section et_pb_section_4 et_pb_with_background et_section_regular">
				
				
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_row et_pb_row_10">
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_4_4 et_pb_column_13  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough et-last-child">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_9  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_light">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner"><h2>What’s a Typical Day at Shaws Braddell Heights Like?</h2></div>
			</div>
			</div>
				
				
				
				
			</div><div class="et_pb_row et_pb_row_11 tablet-reverse">
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_2 et_pb_column_14  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_10  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_light">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner"><p>The day begins at our vast, open field, where the children play with their peers upon arrival. At 8:30am, the children will be gathered from the playground, sandpit and sports areas and ushered into their classroom for circle activity, followed by a morning snack.</p>
<p>Then it’s lesson time! English Curriculum begins, followed by outdoor play, sensory play or gardening, depending on the day of the week. As we follow a <a href="https://shaws.com.sg/curriculum/">play-based curriculum,</a> we ensure that the children explore non-academic activities on top of academic subjects.</p>
<p>After the play session, the children start their Chinese curriculum. We designed small group activities for both English and Chinese lessons for the children to work with their peers or independently. Then it’s break for lunch!</p>
<p>The second half of the day is for children on the full-day programme. The non-nappers will join the Shaws Play Club, where they will engage in a different activity each day. Your children will learn cooking, dive into arts and crafts or pick up a new sport! Every day at Shaws Preschool is a different and fun experience!</p></div>
			</div>
			</div><div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_2 et_pb_column_15  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough et-last-child">

				</video></div>
				
			</div>
			</div>
				
				
				
				
			</div>
				
				
			</div><div id="food-served" class="et_pb_section et_pb_section_5 et_pb_with_background et_section_regular">
				
				
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_row et_pb_row_12">
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_4_4 et_pb_column_16  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough et-last-child">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_11  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_light">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner"><h2>What Do Kids at Shaws Braddell Heights Eat?</h2></div>
			</div>
			</div>
				
				
				
				
			</div><div class="et_pb_row et_pb_row_13">
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_2 et_pb_column_17  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_image et_pb_image_1 box-blue">
				
				
				
				
				<span class="et_pb_image_wrap "><img decoding="async" width="510" height="610" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/What-Do-Kids-at-Shaws-Braddell-Heights-Eat.jpg" alt="" title="What Do Kids at Shaws Braddell Heights Eat" data-srcset="https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/What-Do-Kids-at-Shaws-Braddell-Heights-Eat.jpg 510w, https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/What-Do-Kids-at-Shaws-Braddell-Heights-Eat-480x574.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 510px, 100vw" class="wp-image-11450 lazyload"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="510" height="610" src="https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/What-Do-Kids-at-Shaws-Braddell-Heights-Eat.jpg" alt="" title="What Do Kids at Shaws Braddell Heights Eat" srcset="https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/What-Do-Kids-at-Shaws-Braddell-Heights-Eat.jpg 510w, https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/What-Do-Kids-at-Shaws-Braddell-Heights-Eat-480x574.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 510px, 100vw" class="wp-image-11450 lazyload" /></noscript></span>
			</div>
			</div><div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_2 et_pb_column_18  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough et-last-child">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_12  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_light">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner"><p>Preschool nutrition is important for the little ones to grow! We know different children have different preferences, so we serve a variety of Asian and western food such as pasta and claypot rice. As we are big on healthy eating, we only serve whole grain pasta and rice.</p>
<p>For snack breaks in the morning and afternoon, the children enjoy fruits and biscuits, along with milk. We also make sure that we check with parents on any food allergies that their children may have.</p>
<p>We take nutrition seriously at Shaws and make sure that our children are not served sugary drinks or processed food. This ensures that they will be able to grow and develop healthy and active minds and bodies during their important formative years.</p></div>
			</div><div class="et_pb_button_module_wrapper et_pb_button_12_wrapper et_pb_button_alignment_phone_center et_pb_module ">

			</div>

			</div>
				
				
			</div><div id="our-principal" class="et_pb_section et_pb_section_6 et_pb_with_background et_section_regular">
				
				
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_row et_pb_row_14">
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_4_4 et_pb_column_19  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough et-last-child">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_13  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_light">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner"><h2 style="text-align: center;"><span data-metadata="<!--(figmeta)eyJmaWxlS2V5Ijoid24zaGh5czM3NzVHdXp6RHh5dm0zTiIsInBhc3RlSUQiOjM0MjcxMzgxMiwiZGF0YVR5cGUiOiJzY2VuZSJ9Cg==(/figmeta)-->"></span><span>Meet The Principal of Shaws Braddell Heights!</span></h2></div>
			</div><div class="et_pb_module et_pb_divider et_pb_divider_1 et_pb_divider_position_ et_pb_space"><div class="et_pb_divider_internal"></div></div>
			</div>
				
				
				
				
			</div><div class="et_pb_row et_pb_row_15">
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_2 et_pb_column_20  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_image et_pb_image_2 box-blue">
				
				
				
				
				<span class="et_pb_image_wrap "><img decoding="async" width="510" height="507" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/IQprincipal.jpg" alt="Iqlimah Zain, Shaws Braddell Heights" title="IQprincipal" data-srcset="https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/IQprincipal.jpg 510w, https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/IQprincipal-480x477.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 510px, 100vw" class="wp-image-11436 lazyload"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="510" height="507" src="https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/IQprincipal.jpg" alt="Iqlimah Zain, Shaws Braddell Heights" title="IQprincipal" srcset="https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/IQprincipal.jpg 510w, https://shaws.com.sg/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/IQprincipal-480x477.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 510px, 100vw" class="wp-image-11436 lazyload" /></noscript></span>
			</div>
			</div><div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_2 et_pb_column_21  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough et-last-child">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_14  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_light">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner">Here’s our energetic principal, Iqlimah Zain, fondly known as IQ! With over 17 years of experience in the preschool industry, IQ has long advocated for inclusive education. She believes that education must be holistic and encompassing, with careful consideration of every child’s unique needs.<p></p>
<p>Her vision for Shaws Braddell Heights is to nurture resilient and respectful children in a safe environment by encouraging child-led activities that spur the children to learn and discover the world around them in a self-directed fashion.</p>
<p>In her personal time, IQ is an adrenaline enthusiast who enjoys water rafting, sky-diving and bungee jumping. She feels that the adrenaline rush from these activities helps with her concentration. As a stress buster, she turns to horseback riding. It’s one of her favourite activities when overseas!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></div>
			</div>
			</div>
				
				
				
				
			</div>
				
				
			</div><div id="our-educational-philosophy" class="et_pb_section et_pb_section_7 et_pb_with_background et_section_regular">
				
				
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_row et_pb_row_16">

			</div><div class="et_pb_module et_pb_divider et_pb_divider_2 et_pb_divider_position_ et_pb_space"><div class="et_pb_divider_internal"></div></div>

				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_2 et_pb_column_23  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_16  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_light">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner"><p>About our school’s philosophy, IQ has this to say:</p>
<p>“I believe everyone is unique, and that we all learn differently. As an educator, I have always believed in experiential learning, where children are encouraged to learn and discover new things.&nbsp;</p>
<p>At Shaws Braddell Heights, every day is an adventure! We are definitely not a one-size-fits-all kind of place. All children are inquisitive—the more you do with them, the more they learn. For instance, by growing a garden, our children can learn the process of photosynthesis in an experiential, hands-on manner. This way, they can identify, observe, discover, and retain in their memory how plants grow, and understand what they’ve learned in a faster manner.”</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></div>

				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_18  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_light">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner"><p>Curious to know what were the memorable moments at Shaws? So are we!</p>
<p>Let us take a leaf from the past as Principal IQ shares her treasured memories of Shaws in bygone years.</p>
<p>“My favourite memory was of a carnival a decade ago at the Mountbatten campus where all the five campuses came together for a day of fun and we all got to know each other. It was a treat for the educators to meet the parents and colleagues from the different schools. The best part of the day was seeing the little ones having the time of their lives at the game stations, photo booth and sports area.”</p>
<p>We hope you enjoyed your stay here at the Braddell Heights page and learned a thing or two about our cherished school. Curious to know more? Simply arrange a time with us by filling the form below. We’d love to host you at our cosy premises!</p></div>
